"Smartcards are on the cusp of gaining acceptance in corporations but a major stumbling block to their widespread use is the number of cards, that users have to manage. The way around this is to integrate a number of applications into a single card. Paul Brettle argues that the integration of smartcards into corporate life is the way forward. There are some necessary criteria for successful integration and also certain trappings to be wary of in integration systems. This article examines the use of smartcards in corporations, how smartcards should be integrated and how to avoid failure."
